@startuml
title Event loop — primary click on `Initial` advances to `ComparisonChart`

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor User
participant "BrandDesignUpdate-\nWelcomePage\n(Fragment)" as Frag
participant "BrandDesignUpdate-\nPageViewModel" as VM
participant "LinearOnboarding-\nOrchestrator" as Orch
participant "currentStep\n(IsolatedStep)" as Step

== Initial render (already InProgress(Initial)) ==

Orch --> VM : state = InProgress(plan, idx)
VM -> Step : currentStep.resolveDialog()
Step --> VM : IsolatedOnboardingDialog.Initial(...)
VM --> Frag : dialogState = Initial(...)
Frag -> Frag : configureDaxCta(Initial(...))

== User taps primary ==

User -> Frag : tap primary CTA
Frag -> VM : onPrimaryCtaClicked()
VM -> Orch : onEvent(OnboardingEvent.PrimaryClicked)
note right of Orch
  Orchestrator never inspects the event.
  Just routes it to currentStep.transition().
end note

Orch -> Step : currentStep.transition(event)
Step --> Orch : Advance

Orch -> Orch : walk plan from idx+1,\nskip steps whose precondition()\nreturns false
Orch -> Orch : update state = InProgress(plan, newIdx)
Orch --> VM : state = InProgress(plan, newIdx)\n[currentStep is now ComparisonChart]

== Re-render ==

VM -> Step : currentStep.resolveDialog()
note right of Step
  Now this is the
  ComparisonChart step.
end note
Step --> VM : IsolatedOnboardingDialog.ComparisonChart(...)
VM --> Frag : dialogState = ComparisonChart(...)
Frag -> Frag : configureDaxCta(ComparisonChart(...))

@enduml
